725155f-a.title: Queens: 27th Avenue - 9th Street.
725155f-a.text:
27th Avenue, north side, just west of 9th Street, showing
the Josiah Blackwell House of 1873. It stands about 160 feet
back of the street on elevated ground. When 8th Street will be
cut through north from 27th Avenue, the wing of the house will
face on that street. 27th Avenue is the former Franklin Avenue,
and 9th Street the former Tardell Street.
Federal Art Project--W.P.A.  May 25, 1937
Berenice Abbott
CREDIN LINE IRERATIVE

725156f-a.title: Queens: 27th Avenue - 9th Street
725156f-a.text:
27th Ave., south side, opposite 9th Street, showing the James
Tisdale mansion. It was erected in 1826 by Samuel Blackwell and
was known as 134 Franklin Street. lIt came into the possession of
James Tisdale, who came from Massachusetts in 1837, through his
Ihmarriage to the daughter of the owner. His son Hobert was the owner
in 1896.
1922.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
